article.description: Scott, Prairie View A&M beat Jackson St, 70-55
article.headline: Scott, Prairie View A&M beat Jackson St, 70-55
article.linkText: Scott, Prairie View A&M beat Jackson St, 70-55
article.story: HOUSTON -- Montrael Scott scored 15 points to lead Prairie View A&M to its fourth-straight win over Jackson State, 70-55, on Saturday. Jayrn Johnson added 11 points for Prairie View (3-14, 1/3 Southwestern Athletic), while Tre Hagood and Jacoby Green scored 10 apiece. Hagood also had eight assists. A pair of free throws by Raeford Worsham with 4:42 left in the first half pulled Jackson State (4-14, 2-3) within five, but a jumper by Scott and a dunk by Johnson sparked a 12-1 run and gave the Panthers a 36-20 lead. Jackson State trailed by double digits the rest of the way. Prairie View made 23 of 49 (46.9 percent) field goals, including 8 of 16 from 3-point range, while the Tigers shot just 32.8 percent and 2 of 18 (11.1 percent) from deep. Derrell Taylor led Jackson State with 18 points.
